  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently, Remix does not provide much of a useful output on transaction revert, even if you choose to force-run the transaction. The output basically is 1 line stating the error:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntransact to XXXXXX.(fallback) errored: Error: VM Exception while processing transaction: reverted with reason string 'IIA'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere are various scenarios when one may need to actually force-run the tx and then work with it, eg. even to debug directly in Remix. Currently I have to go to my client logs to retrieve the hash to further trace / debug. It would have been useful to provide at least some generic info on the revert, most importantly the mined tx hash, and maybe gas usage. ",
